South Africa based ultra-high resolution geophysical surveys specialist Xcalibur Airborne Geophysics (Xcalibur) has been awarded a World Bank sponsored magnetic and radiometric mapping project for the government of Burkina Faso, MD SIMON BOSCH tells SASCHA SOLOMONS. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 7 2018. It will be published online on the 6th August 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy